The President gave a speech at the White House to celebrate Greek independence and the contributions of Greek and Greek Americans to the United States. He expressed his gratitude to the Greek Orthodox Archdiocese of America and highlighted the importance of democracy and the Greek idea of "know thyself" in American society. The President also acknowledged the courage and character of Greek immigrants and emphasized the need to protect and champion democracy in the face of its foes. He spoke optimistically about the future and the opportunity to work together for a better world. The President ended his speech by thanking the Greek American community for their loyalty and support throughout his career. After the speech, there was a musical performance by Rita Wilson, followed by remarks from actor Tom Hanks, who humorously mentioned his marriage to a Greek woman. The event concluded with a reception.